{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":107692,"duration_api_ms":107508,"num_turns":21,"result":"Here's a summary of the git history analysis:\n\n**Hotspots:** `lib/config.sh` (13), `lib/agent.sh` (12), and `ultrainit.sh` (10) are the busiest files after `README.md` (14). The entire `lib/` directory is the core churn zone.\n\n**Temporal coupling:** `lib/agent.sh` ↔ `lib/config.sh` is the tightest pair (6 co-changes). The core lib modules (`agent`, `config`, `gather`, `research`, `synthesize`) are highly coupled — changes to one almost always ripple to others. `README.md` ↔ `ultrainit.sh` also move together (4 times), suggesting docs are kept in sync with CLI changes.\n\n**Bug-fix density:** `lib/research.sh` and `lib/config.sh` have the most fix commits (4 each), followed by `lib/agent.sh` (3). These are the most error-prone files.\n\n**Ownership diffusion:** Single author (`Joel Barmettler`) — no diffusion to report. All files are owned by one person.\n\n**Recent activity:** `lib/` dominates with ~68 changes, followed by root-level files (~35), then `tests/` (~20). All activity is recent since this is a young repo.\n\n**Commit patterns:** Conventional commits are used (feat:, fix:, test:) but inconsistently — some commits use free-form prose. GitHub PR numbers (#1, #2) are referenced in merge commits but no JIRA-style tickets.\n\n**Branch patterns:** `feat/<kebab-case>` and `fix/<kebab-case>` — clean two-segment convention matching the conventional commit types.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"afd663fd-7da5-4b90-bfcc-6b2fc072b398","total_cost_usd":0.3800942,"usage":{"input_tokens":19,"cache_creation_input_tokens":37908,"cache_read_input_tokens":430026,"output_tokens":6417,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":37908,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":407,"cache_read_input_tokens":33292,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3507,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3507},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":19,"outputTokens":6417,"cacheReadInputTokens":430026,"cacheCreationInputTokens":37908,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.3674748,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":13,"outputTokens":889,"cacheReadInputTokens":43639,"cacheCreationInputTokens":3038,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.0126194,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01SJzVGRxosyV837poAuRKJB","tool_input":{"command":"git log --pretty=format:\"%H\" | while read commit; do\n  git diff-tree --no-commit-id -r --name-only \"$commit\" 2>/dev/null\ndone | awk '{files[NR]=$0} END {\n  for (i=1; i<=NR; i++) {\n    for (j=i+1; j<=NR; j++) {\n      # Only files from same commit would need tracking - use different approach\n    }\n  }\n}' 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"\n# Better approach: process commits one at a time\ngit log --pretty=format:\"%H\" | head -50 | while read commit; do\n  files=$(git diff-tree --no-commit-id -r --name-only \"$commit\" 2>/dev/null | tr '\\n' ' ')\n  echo \"$files\"\ndone | awk '{\n  n=split($0, files, \" \")\n  for (i=1; i<=n; i++) {\n    for (j=i+1; j<=n; j++) {\n      if (files[i] < files[j]) key = files[i] \" | \" files[j]\n      else key = files[j] \" | \" files[i]\n      count[key]++\n    }\n  }\n} END {\n  for (k in count) print count[k], k\n}' | sort -rn | head -10","description":"Find temporal coupling - file pairs that change together"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01Bk7bJkiRYXuH9hTqpGvnh5","tool_input":{"command":"git log --since=\"30 days ago\" --pretty=format: --name-only | grep \"/\" | sed 's|/[^/]*$||' | sort | uniq -c | sort -rn | head -20","description":"Recent activity by directory"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_012TmiTv9VFcKPuxppxYpJvN","tool_input":{"command":"git log --since=\"30 days ago\" --pretty=format: --name-only | grep \"/\" | awk -F/ '{\n  if (NF==2) print $1\n  else if (NF>=3) print $1\"/\"$2\n}' | sort | uniq -c | sort -rn | head -20","description":"Recent activity by directory"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01CAmtewJDJfBWazqL1gvz1S","tool_input":{"command":"git log --pretty=format:\"%H\" | while read commit; do\n  git diff-tree --no-commit-id -r --name-only \"$commit\" 2>/dev/null | tr '\\n' ' '\n  echo\ndone | grep -v \"^$\" | head -60 > /tmp/commit_files.txt\npython3 -c \"\nfrom collections import defaultdict\npairs = defaultdict(int)\nwith open('/tmp/commit_files.txt') as f:\n    for line in f:\n        files = line.strip().split()\n        files = [x for x in files if x]\n        for i in range(len(files)):\n            for j in range(i+1, len(files)):\n                a,b = sorted([files[i], files[j]])\n                pairs[(a,b)] += 1\nfor (a,b),c in sorted(pairs.items(), key=lambda x: -x[1])[:10]:\n    print(c, a, '|', b)\n\"","description":"Find temporal coupling using Python"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01TAntHKUnk7zfvfHXsnRETu","tool_input":{"command":"git log --format=\"%H %s\" | head -50 > /tmp/commits.txt && wc -l /tmp/commits.txt","description":"Export commits to file"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01RZBEb1GD91s2AGjrNSnChd","tool_input":{"command":"git log --format=\"%H\" > /tmp/all_commits.txt && echo \"done\"","description":"Export all commit hashes"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_0188e585g9zrdeAgeP5wfA2e","tool_input":{"command":"while IFS= read -r commit; do\n  files=$(git diff-tree --no-commit-id -r --name-only \"$commit\" 2>/dev/null | tr '\\n' '|')\n  if [ -n \"$files\" ]; then echo \"$files\"; fi\ndone < .ultrainit/all_commits.txt > .ultrainit/commit_file_lists.txt && wc -l .ultrainit/commit_file_lists.txt","description":"Build per-commit file lists"}}],"structured_output":{"hotsp